<paragraph blockId="37.[168,778,1800,2091]" lastBlockId="37.[810,1420,1801,1925]" pageId="37" pageNumber="218">
and adaxial surfaces both sparsely hairy, with glandular hairs; margins ciliate. Inflorescence a solitary flower or a cyme, with 2 or 3 flowers. Pedicels hairy. Sepals 5; 4.0– 
<quantity box="[215,301,1900,1924]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[378,512,1900,1924]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2.5 mm</quantity>
wide; ovate or lanceolate; purplish green or reddish-purple; surface hairy, with glandular hairs; margins ciliate; apices obtuse or rounded. Petals 5; 3.0– 
<quantity box="[422,506,2000,2024]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[578,709,2000,2024]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–2.5 mm</quantity>
wide; oblanceolate or obovate; unlobed; pale yellow. Androecium with 9–10 stamens and 
<quantity box="[495,627,2067,2091]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.8 mm</quantity>
long anthers. Gynoecium with 2 styles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[810,1420,1801,1925]" pageId="37" pageNumber="218">
Characteristics allowing to distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[1288,1420,1835,1859]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cespitosa">
<emphasis box="[1288,1420,1835,1859]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="218">S. cespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the other 
<taxonomicName box="[982,1176,1868,1892]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[982,1088,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="218">Saxifraga</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
present on Ellesmere Island can be found under 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1199,1902,1925]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="37" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cernua">
<emphasis box="[1096,1199,1902,1925]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="218">S. cernua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
